<body>
 <h3>Rule-4 ᐅ </h3>
 <p>Imperative Sentence-এর ক্ষেত্রে passive voice-এর structure ᐅ </p>
 <p>1. Main verb দিয়ে শুরু হওয়া Sentence-এর ক্ষেত্রে ᐅ </p>
 <card>Let+ Object’s subject + be+ verb’s past participle</card>
 <h3>Example ᐅ </h3>
 <ul>
  <li>Write the article. (Active)</li>
  <li>Let the article be written. (Passive)</li>
 </ul>
 <ul>
  <li>Prepare the assignment. (Active)</li>
  <li>Let the assignment be prepared. (Passive)</li>
 </ul>
 <br>
 <p>2. “Do not” দিয়ে শুরু হওয়া Sentence-এর ক্ষেত্রে ᐅ </p>
 <card>Let not + Object’s subject + be+ verb’s past participle</card>
 <h3>Example ᐅ </h3>
 <ul>
  <li>Do not write the article. (Active)</li>
  <li>Let not the article be written. (Passive)</li>
 </ul>
 <ul>
  <li>Do not prepare the assignment. (Active)</li>
  <li>Let not the assignment be prepared. (Passive)</li>
 </ul>
 <br>
 <p>3. Sentence “Let” দিয়ে শুরু হলে এবং এর পর personal object যেমন: me/us/him/her/you/them থাকলে ᐅ </p>
 <card>Let+ Object’s subject + be + verb’s past participle+ personal object</card>
 <h3>Example ᐅ </h3>
 <ul>
  <li>Let me write the article. (Active)</li>
  <li>Let the article be written by me. (Passive)</li>
 </ul>
 <ul>
  <li>Let him write the letter. (Active)</li>
  <li>Let the letter be written by him. (Passive)</li>
 </ul>
 <br>
 <p>4. “Never” দিয়ে শুরু হওয়া Sentence-এর ক্ষেত্রে ᐅ </p>
 <card>Let not + Object’s subject + ever be + verb’s past participle</card>
 <h3>Example ᐅ </h3>
 <ul>
  <li>Never deceive anyone. (Active)</li>
  <li>Let not anyone ever be deceived. (Passive)</li>
 </ul>
 <ul>
  <li>Never go there. (Active)</li>
  <li>Let not there ever be gone. (Passive)</li>
 </ul>
 <br>
 <p>5. Sentence main verb দিয়ে শুরু হলে এবং এর পর personal object যেমন: me/us/him/her/you/them থাকলে ᐅ </p>
 <card>Let+ direct object + be+ verb’s past participle + for + personal object</card>
 <h3>Example ᐅ </h3>
 <ul>
  <li>Give me a pencil. (Active)</li>
  <li>Let a pencil be given for me. (Passive)</li>
 </ul>
 <ul>
  <li>Give me an eraser. (Active)</li>
  <li>Let an eraser be given for me. (Passive)</li>
 </ul>
